cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: The paper deals with information theory and its generalization to multiple variables. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also proposes a new measure of redundancy and uses it to decompose multivariate information, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the lattice structure of the redundancy measure, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
